Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_time_unit(25.10)                                      get_time_unit(25.10)

Name
       get_time_unit  - Returns the current time unit (in nanoseconds) for the
       session derived from the library file or set  with  the  setLibraryUnit
       -time parameter

Syntax
       get_time_unit

       Returns  the current time unit (in nanoseconds) for the session derived
       from the library file or set with the setLibraryUnit  -time  parameter.
       This  unit  will  be  used during report generation and constraint set-
       tings.

Parameters
       -help  Prints out the command usage.

Example
              * The following command returns the time unit for the session:

                get_time_unit

                1.000000ns

Related Information
              * setLibraryUnit

